    <div class="documentTop">        
        
        <h1>Department of Government Services</h1>
        
        <div class="pageDescription"><p>The Department of Government Services has a number of subordinate enterprises taking care of central service functions for the ministries and the government. The department offers advice and recommendations on how the government should manage its responsibility in different sectors. This concerns e.g. issues like the governing, organizing, regionalizing and division of labour between different sorts of government organs, independent government agencies and private businesses. The aim is to ensure that government acts according to a comprehensive policy, with continuity and effectiveness. The department is also working to develop better governing tools and acts as an advisor on how the management of different government agencies should be conducted.</p>
<p>The department has these subordinate enterprises:</p>
<ul>
<li>The County Governors (fylkesmenn) - administrative responsibility </li>
<li>The Directorate of Public Construction and Property (Statsbygg) </li>
<li>Government Administration Services (Departementenes servicesenter) </li>
<li>The Norwegian Public Service Pension Fund (Statens Pensjonskasse) </li>
<li>The Data Inspectorate (Datatilsynet) </li>
<li>Statskonsult - a state-owned limited company specializing in public management issues<br /></li></ul></div>        
